  "title": "Documentation missing of how to implement debounce in searchBox widget",
  "body": "[The documentation for the searchBox widget](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#searchbox) says:\n\n![unbenannt](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/36167/13920180/02668938-ef72-11e5-93bb-65a1ddfafbfd.PNG)\n\nBut how exactly must it be implemented? Does `queryHook` expect a (debounced) return? If so, what? object, function, bool? \n\nCalling a [debounce/deferr/throttle](https://code.openhub.net/file?fid=B6-cenRVoJ7qDbRegFtkguIsHY0&cid=uXtUw5YhiiU&s=&fp=305271&mp&projSelected=true#L0) function inside queryHook seems not to work.\n\n```\n    queryHook:function(query, search) {\n        $.debounce(search(query), 1000);\n        return false; // ? \n    }\n```\n",
